# Version 1 — Original Sheet Structure

> *26 columns. Built iteratively. Every column earned its place.*

[View the live Google Sheet here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1LqhETkG8e6kEHTJIhSYnzvjWfyH5cplcZrpqmlW9m4U/edit?usp=sharing)

---

## Overview

This document captures the original prototype of the task management system — built from scratch, column by column, as new requirements emerged from real usage.

The goal was simple: a functional, data-driven personal productivity tracker that could capture task details, automate date tracking, and calculate meaningful KPIs. No templates. No shortcuts. Just building something real and learning as we went.

The prototype was built iteratively — functionality first, architecture second. Each column was added as a new need surfaced, resulting in a system that worked effectively as a standalone tracker but wasn't built to scale, integrate with external tools, or support a team.

What it did prove was the core concept — automated task tracking, real-time KPI calculation, and performance monitoring are all achievable inside Google Sheets.

This document exists as a record of what was built and the foundation for understanding why a redesign became necessary.

