## What This Taught Us

Building across 26 columns without a planned architecture worked — until it didn't.

Every column made sense when it was added. But over time, the sheet became a single flat structure trying to do everything at once. No separation between raw data and calculated outputs. No clear flow. No room to grow.

That's not a failure — that's exactly what a prototype is supposed to teach you.

**The lesson: structure your data model before you build, not after.**

Version 2 takes everything this sheet proved was possible and rebuilds it on a foundation designed to last.

